  <releases>
    <release version="2.0.0" date="2026-02-20">
      <url type="details">https://github.com/CleoMenezesJr/Serigy/releases/tag/2.0.0</url>
      <description translate="no">
        <p><b>Major technical overhaul and paradigm shift:</b></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Core refactored for type safety, modularity, and GObject property usage.</li>
          <li>UI rebuilt: slots now use GridView, modern dark theme CSS, and improved image slot readability.</li>
          <li>Clipboard monitoring optimized for performance and memory; memory leaks and quit/background issues resolved.</li>
          <li>New features: incognito mode, auto-clear for expired clipboard items, tooltips, context menus with pin/copy formatting, and global shortcut display.</li>
          <li>Internationalization: full translation coverage for Brazilian Portuguese, Russian, and now Spanish (Chile); terminology standardized and translation infrastructure modernized.</li>
          <li><b>Paradigm shift:</b> Serigy is no longer just a clipboard pinnerâ€”it's now a minimal, efficient clipboard manager.</li>
          <li>UX polish: improved feedback, toast messages, clarified action labels, and more responsive dialogs.</li>
          <li>Build/runtime: updated to Blueprint 0.19.0, GNOME runtime 49, and improved logging/debugging.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
